    • Field Detail

      • DEFAULT_GROUP_LABEL

        public static final String DEFAULT_GROUP_LABEL
        A label used to identify the default groups. If the label of an element is not a key in the map, the keys associated with label are used instead.

        Hint: For backwards compatibility either Grouping.DEFAULT_VERTEX_LABEL_GROUP or Grouping.DEFAULT_EDGE_LABEL_GROUP may be used instead.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • addKeyToElement

        public void addKeyToElement(T element,
                            Object key)
        Description copied from interface: KeyFunction
        Store a key on an element.

        This is used to store the grouping key on the super element after grouping.

        The default implementation of this function does not change the element.

        Specified by:
        addKeyToElement in interface KeyFunction<T extends Element,org.apache.flink.api.java.tuple.Tuple>
        Parameters:
        element - The element where the key should be stored.
        key - The key to store on the element. The type of the key is expected to be the same as the type of keys extracted by this key function.
